member.name: FDICABINETINFO
member.summary: The FDICABINETINFO structure contains details about a particular cabinet file.

member.name: FDICABINETINFO.cbCabinet
member.summary: The total length of the cabinet file.

member.name: FDICABINETINFO.cFolders
member.summary: The count of the folders in the cabinet.

member.name: FDICABINETINFO.cFiles
member.summary: The count of the files in the cabinet.

member.name: FDICABINETINFO.setID
member.summary: The identifier of the cabinet set.

member.name: FDICABINETINFO.iCabinet
member.summary: The cabinet number in set. This index is zero based.

member.name: FDICABINETINFO.fReserve
member.summary: If this value is set to TRUE, a reserved area is present in the cabinet.

member.name: FDICABINETINFO.hasprev
member.summary: If this value is set to TRUE, the cabinet is linked to a previous cabinet. This is accomplished by having a file continued from the previous cabinet into the current one.

member.name: FDICABINETINFO.hasnext
member.summary: If this value is set to TRUE, the current cabinet is linked to the next cabinet by having a file continued from the current cabinet into the next one.
